cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper presents a new approach to computing the diffusion geometry, which is a commonly used method for manifold learning in machine learning and computer vision. The paper focuses on improving the efficiency of the method, making it more suitable for analyzing big datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves some computational aspects, which suggest that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
